race.comment: OCEANELLA (2) made progress last season, and resumed with a big finishing second as the favourite at Kyneton 3 weeks ago over this trip. She has a superior gate and can have the last say this time. LOTTA CITY (10) was second on debut and then went to Stony Creek, brimming with confidence, only to strike a heavy track. She tried hard that day, but can be forgiven. Go again from the pole position here. Follow your money. FEARLESS MONARCH (1) did well during a winter campaign and will be a lot stronger now.  A couple of jumpouts will have her ready to run a big race fresh up in this. Include. TOO MUCH TOO SOON (14) is trained on the track, and will be better after her fresh up fourth at Moe 18 days ago. Each way. ANGELISTA (6) is making her debut and should be respected, especially if the money comes for her.
